getFixes

public java.util.Collection<QuickFix> getFixes()
Returns a list of zero or more Action objects that can be used to fix the current warning. The actions are displayed in the status report when the user clicks the "quick fix" button. If a quick-fix was successful, it should set the "SUCCESS" property of the action to Boolean.TRUE. Warnings that were successfully fixed will be removed from the list.

Returns:
a collection of fixes
